column5:
Preheat oven to 350*; 
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients (flour through salt) in a large bowl.  
Stir in carrot and next 5 ingredients (Carrot through
pineapple); 
Combine oil and next 4 ingredients (oil through egg
whites); stir with a whisk until just moist.  Spoon into 24 muffin cups coated with cooking spray.  Bake at 350* for 25 minutes or until muffins spring back when touched lightly in center.  Remove muffins from pans immediately; cool on a wire rack.

Heat grill to medium; Remove stems from mushrooms.  Rinse and dry;

Whisk vinegar, olive oil and basil together.  Brush each cap with mixture, place on grill, bottom up.  Brush inside of each cap.  Grill 3 minutes, then turn.  Place cheese over each cap, and continue to cook until the cheese melts, about 2 minutes.  Remove

Place each cap on a bun and top with a tomato slice, lettuce leaf and any desired condiments.

Combine egg and buttermil;
Combine 1/4 cup flour, cornmeal salt, pepper; Dredge tomato slices in remaining 1/4 cup flour; dip in egg mixture, and dredge in cornmeal mixture.

Pour oil  to a depth of 1/4 to 1/2" in large cast iron skillet; heat to 375*.  Drop tomatoes in batches into hot oil, and cook 2 minutes on each side until golden.  Drain on paper towels or rack.  Sprinkle hot tomatoes with salt.

Layer:
Lettuce, pat down, tomatoes, chicken avocado, onions, shrimp;
Pat down more and pour dressing over top.
Refrigerate at least one hour;
top with bacon and serve.

*Too heavy on dressing to use the whole pint.

Fry bacon and saute chiopped onion and celery;
Add other ingredients to large pot with water to cover.  Cook until vegetables are soft, remove bay leaves.
Use stick blender, then cube and add about 1/2 pound processed cheese and half and half.

Crush wafers and mix with other dry ingredients;
Beat eggs separately and then stir into dry ingredients;
Add milk, butter and nuts;
Bake in a greased tube pan at 275 degrees for 2 hours.
